## Phase 4 — Core Migration (one cache at a time)

```
## Task: Migrate ONE cache from EhCache RMI to Kafka — implement changes

We are replacing EhCache RMI sync with Kafka for cache synchronisation.
Infrastructure is already in place (KafkaConfig.java, CacheSyncMessage.java, 
build.gradle, application.yml all updated in Phase 3).

### Reference Files
- Custom CacheManager : #file:src/main/java/<path>/CacheManager.java
- Kafka config        : #file:src/main/java/<path>/config/KafkaConfig.java
- CacheSyncMessage    : #file:src/main/java/<path>/cache/CacheSyncMessage.java
- EhCache config      : #file:src/main/resources/ehcache.xml

### Target cache for this run
CACHE NAME: <fill in one cache name from Phase 1 output>
KAFKA STRATEGY: <Invalidate-only | Push full value>  (from Phase 1 output)
TOPIC NAME: <from Phase 2 output>

### What to implement

#### 1. Producer side — on cache write
In CacheManager.java:
- Inject KafkaTemplate<String, String> (use constructor injection)
- Find the write path for the target cache (put / update / remove methods)
- After the existing EhCache write, publish a CacheSyncMessage to the topic:
  - For Push strategy: populate cacheName, action=PUT/REMOVE, key, value 
    (serialise value to JSON using ObjectMapper)
  - For Invalidate-only strategy: populate cacheName, action=RELOAD or INVALIDATE, 
    key only — no value field
- Wrap Kafka publish in try-catch — a Kafka failure must NOT break the cache write
  Log the error but allow the operation to continue
- Do NOT remove the existing EhCache put/remove call yet — 
  both should run in parallel during migration

#### 2. Consumer side — on receiving sync event
Create a new class: 
src/main/java/<base-package>/cache/CacheSyncConsumer.java
- Annotate with @Component
- Inject the custom CacheManager
- Add a @KafkaListener method for the target cache topic
- In the listener:
  - Deserialise the incoming message to CacheSyncMessage using ObjectMapper
  - Check the action field:
    - PUT → call the appropriate CacheManager method to update local cache with 
      the provided value (Push strategy only)
    - RELOAD / INVALIDATE → call the appropriate CacheManager method to 
      evict and reload from DB
    - REMOVE → evict the key from local cache
  - Skip processing if the message originates from this instance 
    (add instanceId field to CacheSyncMessage and compare — 
    generate instanceId as a @Value injected UUID at startup)
  - Wrap in try-catch — a bad message must not crash the consumer

#### 3. Inner CacheEventListener for this cache
- Find the inner listener class inside CacheManager.java 
  that corresponds to the target cache
- Comment it out (do NOT delete yet) with a note:
  // MIGRATION: replaced by Kafka producer in <date> — remove after validation

### Rules
- Only modify code related to the ONE named cache above
- Do not touch other caches or their listener classes
- Do not remove ehcache.xml config for this cache yet
- After completing, print a checklist:
  [ ] Producer publishes on write
  [ ] Consumer receives and applies update
  [ ] instanceId self-message guard in place
  [ ] Kafka failure does not break cache write
  [ ] Old RMI listener commented out (not deleted)
  
### Repeat instruction
This prompt should be re-run once per cache, changing only the 
TARGET CACHE FOR THIS RUN section each time.
